hat the typical rms-flux relation is\nmainly generated by these fluctuations. In general a higher rms is generated by\na larger amount of superposed flares which is compatible with a higher mass\naccretion rate expressed by a larger flux.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Dec 2014 16:46:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
