axies. In this model, the decrease in the cross-correlation signal\nfrom 250 {\\mu}m to 500 {\\mu}m comes from the fact that the galaxies that are\nprimarily contributing to 500 {\\mu}m fluctuations peak at a higher redshift\nthan those at 250 {\\mu}m.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Dec 2014 14:57:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Dec 2014 15:15:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-07"}
